OL,3,CRobert Peston: Is this Starmer's
OL,4,CWaterloo?
OL,6,FHe has said this morning he will not
OL,7,Fbow out quietly, and would participate
OL,8,Fin a contest. So we are in for a
OL,9,Ftumultuous few days.
OL,11,FTo be clear, MPs tell me they admire
OL,12,FStarmer's performance in his "don't
OL,13,Fsack me speech" this morning.
OL,15,FHe was cheerful and resilient, even as
OL,16,Fhe showed contrition for his party's
OL,17,Fhistorically terrible performance in
OL,18,Flast week's elections.
OL,26,@tD@^OUuD@OO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
