OL,3,CRobert Peston: Is this Starmer's
OL,4,CWaterloo?
OL,6,FSo Starmer's team are braced for more
OL,7,Fpressure on him to announce a so-
OL,8,Fcalled "orderly" timetable for a
OL,9,Fleadership contest.
OL,11,FThe announcement of such a timetable
OL,12,Fmay be all he can do to avoid what he
OL,13,Fsays he wants to prevent at all costs,
OL,14,Fnamely, open and chaotic revolt
OL,15,Fagainst him.
OL,26,@pD@HOUpD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
