OL,3,CRobert Peston: Is this Starmer's
OL,4,CWaterloo?
OL,6,FBy the way, the burn towards any
OL,7,Fannouncement of his announcement may
OL,8,Fbe a few days, because all MPs would
OL,9,Flike to prevent the King from being
OL,10,Fembarrassed by Starmer being in the
OL,11,Fmidst of a life-and-death struggle to
OL,12,Fsave himself, before or when the
OL,13,Fmonarch announces the new legislative
OL,14,Fprogramme in parliament on Wednesday.
OL,16,FStarmer's speech was held in Waterloo.
OL,17,FHe wants to be Wellington, but he may
OL,18,Fbe Napoleon.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
